    note_en: "There is a document on my computer called 'what am I actually doing.docx.' It was last modified in 2018. The answer in the document, as best as I can remember — I've stopped opening it — is approximately twelve pages long. That is the problem the document was trying to solve. You cannot name your way out of a question about names.\n\nThe week I finished my dissertation, I had stopped calling it a dissertation. I had stopped calling it anything. There was just a thing I was writing in the mornings, in a café on the Yangpu waterfront in Shanghai, because the writing was interesting. The chapter I wrote that week is the only chapter I'm still proud of. The rest I can barely remember. They were all correctly named. That was the problem.",
